0,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d192066-Reviews-or0-Washington_Mayfair_Hotel-London_England.html#REVIEWS,"Washington Mayfair Hotel Reviews, London",Diabolical Excuse for Champaign Afternoon Tea,"23-May-2021, The champainge afternoon tea for two, was disgusting, to say the least. The finger sandwiches were made from the cheapest of breads with the crust on. The filling could barely be found, the taste of cheap margarine was all that could be distinguished. The cheese filling was processed from a tube. The ham was also the cheapest available and barely any. The egg and mayonnaise was boiled egg white in a greasy mess. When we thought things couldn't get nastier the scones and cakes arrived, we didn't recognise the scones and had to ask what they were, they looked like fat biscuits brought home from school by a 5 year old attempting their first bake. The other offerings were all the cheapest shop bought. the Brownie bites were still frozen, there was couple of big yellow lumps of what I think might have been cake and rest was most unappealing. The Champaign  was a nasty sweet Prosecco. The cups and saucers mismatched, which is acceptable in a country tea room, but not a so called 5 star Mayfair establishment. When we demanded to see the manger, she told us bare faced lies, telling us the scones had been made by the chef, when challenged she corrected to somebody else made them, but didn't seem to know who, no qualified professional would have allowed any of these offerings out of the kitchen. It was a very strange experience, we were the only guests, it was obvious there had been no visitors for a very longtime and there was no one staying at the hotel. I'm mystified as to why they accepted the booking, if the hotel is not open. The only positive is the waitress she was a delight.‚Ä¶",Date of stay: May 2021,1.0
